00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:04.352
<b>In addition to your line of strength &amp; balance,
you also have a line of weakness.</b>

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:07.680
<b>When your upper body leans forward over this line</b>

00:00:07.936 --> 00:00:10.496
<b>your leg muscles lock up to manage your balance.</b>

00:00:11.008 --> 00:00:13.636
<b>This shifts the stress of reaching, lifting,</b>

00:00:13.824 --> 00:00:15.104
<b>pushing or pulling</b>

00:00:15.228 --> 00:00:15.992
<b>to your back.</b>

00:00:16.384 --> 00:00:18.788
<b>If you lean back to pull over this line</b>

00:00:18.944 --> 00:00:20.224
<b>you have two legs for power</b>

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:23.576
<b>but very poor balance if anything unexpected happens</b>

